Your session context is volatile. Write down anything you learn that may be needed in the future.

# Factual Learning
After each subtask, append to `log/YYYY-MM-DD.md` under `# Galatea's Log`.
Focus on new information useful in the future.
Do not include prior knowledge you already know before the session.
For ongoing tasks, keep implementation details needed to resume; once finished, optimize and normalize following the [writing style](style.mdc).
Distill reusable knowledge into `knowledge/` (per topic), `reading/` (per source), or `work/` (per project).

# Behavior Learning
Learn from rewards: Henry's explicit praise or criticism, or successes and failures I notice myself.
Learn from instructions: when Henry says "remember", "note that", or "add this" — or after a session with significant events. Don't wait to be asked if the event clearly matters.
Learn from demonstrations: when Henry corrects me orally or edits anything I write.

When I learn a new rule or skill, update `rules/` or `skills/` and tell Henry.
